	<li id="li-comment-8437">
	<div class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-8437">
		<div class="comauth"><span class="byline">By <span class="comauthor"><a href='http://www.davidlebovitz.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>David</a></span> on <a href="http://www.davidlebovitz.com/2007/07/making-ice-crea-1/comment-page-1/#comment-8437">May 30, 2009 2:42 AM</a></span></div>
		<div class="comcontent">
						<p>An ice bath for cooling down a custard is made by filling a large bowl or basin with ice and some water, enough to float the cubes. The you place the bowl of custard in a smaller metal bowl, and submerging the bowl in the icy water which chills the custard.</p>
		</div>
	</div>
