	<li id="li-comment-8452">
	<div class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-8452">
		<div class="comauth"><span class="byline">By <span class="comauthor"><a href='http://www.davidlebovitz.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>david</a></span> on <a href="http://www.davidlebovitz.com/2007/07/making-ice-crea-1/comment-page-1/#comment-8452">October 12, 2009 3:43 AM</a></span></div>
		<div class="comcontent">
						<p>hi ellen: Because the ice cream isn&#8217;t churned in the traditional manner, ie: in a machine which incorporates air into the mixture, it&#8217;ll be much firmer when frozen. If you use an electric hand mixer, that helps. You may also want to check out the post on making homemade ice cream softer, which is linked at the end of the post.</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</li>
