	<li id="li-comment-8468">
	<div class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-8468">
		<div class="comauth"><span class="byline">By <span class="comauthor"><a href='http://www.davidlebovitz.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>David</a></span> on <a href="http://www.davidlebovitz.com/2007/07/making-ice-crea-1/comment-page-1/#comment-8468">July 4, 2010 5:10 AM</a></span></div>
		<div class="comcontent">
						<p>Kristina: Ice cream made using this method will not have the same creamy texture of ice cream churned in a machine, but if you have an immersion hand (stick) mixer you can eliminate some of the ice crystals using that. Because the size and density of various mixtures, and the temperature of freezers vary, it&#8217;s impossible to predict exact times when you should stir itâ€”it&#8217;s best just to keep an eye on it and stir it as it freezes.</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</li>
